      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BULLETPROOF KID (1) resumes after finishing fifth at his latest appearance at this track on April 3. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw. Ideally placed and is sure to prove tough to beat. HELLOVATIME (4) finished fourth last start, beaten 4.5 metres at Shepparton over 2190m. Expecting a very good run. ROCKY PACIFIC NZ (7) broke last start and finished a distant last over 1720m at Melton, following a solid second to commence this prep. Must overcome a very wide draw. Meets a similar line up so if he behaves a big run is likely. KISS ME MINI NZ (10) won two starts ago then things went amiss last start when she broke and finished 10 metres away in fifth over 2240m at Melton. Not drawn to best so may need a 10/10 drive. This doesn't look as hard so she is capable of turning things around.",
